README

checker.java

----------------------PROGRAM DESCRIPTION-----------------------

This is a Checker game. You can play it in single player or multi-
player mode.

Single player will be playing with an AI that runs Alpha-Beta
search to look for the best move against opponent.

Piece to move is selected by typing in the position of the piece.
If you want to choose the piece at row 5 column 0, just type in
50. To move it to row 4 column 1, type 41 when prompted.

The game terminates when one side loses its the pieces or when
user key in 'exit' when asked which piece to move.


----------------------------HOW TO------------------------------

The program should be compiled in terminal(have to be in correct
directory first) with the line below:

	javac checker.java


Then run it by calling: 

	java checker



